# Docker build-context exclusions (M10.3 iter-1).
#
# Without this file every `docker compose build` uploads the repo-root
# `.env` to the Docker daemon as part of the build context, leaking
# operator-provisioned secrets to the daemon (and any daemon-side cache
# / image-layer tar) even though no Dockerfile references them.
# Addresses the iter-1 codex P2 finding.
#
# Patterns mirror .gitignore plus build-output dirs that explode the
# context size needlessly.

# Secrets — every form .env.example documents.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
secrets/

# Git metadata (heavy; never referenced by a build).
.git/
.gitignore

# Build outputs (the build stage regenerates these inside the image).
bin/
dist/
coverage/
coverage.out
coverage.html
node_modules/

# IDE / OS noise.
.idea/
.vscode/
*.iml
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Claude Code / OMC harness artefacts (already .gitignored at repo
# root but worth duplicating here in case an operator pulls a fresh
# clone before the global rule fires).
.claude/
.omc/

# Test fixtures + runbook drill outputs.
runtime.test
*.log

# Lessons / docs are referenced by the build only via COPY layers
# that name them explicitly; the broader docs tree is dead-weight.
docs/
